The '''rockrunner''' ('''''Achaetops pycnopygius'''''), also known as the  '''Damara rock-jumper''', is a species of [[Macrosphenidae|African warbler]], formerly placed in the family [[Sylviidae]].<ref name=itis_species>{{ITIS|id=558398 |taxon=Achaetops pycnopygius|accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref> It is the only member of the monotypic genus '''''Achaetops'''''.<ref name=itis_genus>{{ITIS|id=557376 |taxon=Achaetops |accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref>
It is found in [[Angola]] and [[Namibia]].<ref name="iucn status 13 November 2021" />

